1. Dimension Tables
gold.dim_company
Contains descriptive attributes for companies listed in the database. Acts as the primary filtering dimension for all fact tables.
Column Name,Data Type,Key Type,Description,Example
company_id,INT,PK,Unique internal identifier for the company.,1
ticker,VARCHAR,,Stock market symbol (ticker) used on the exchange.,"XTB, CDP"
company_name,VARCHAR,,Full registered name of the company.,XTB S.A.
sector,VARCHAR,,Broad economic sector classification.,Technology
industry,VARCHAR,,Specific line of business within the sector.,Software & Services
 ### `[gold].[fact_results]`

| Column Name | Data Type | Key | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `result_key` | `BIGINT` | **PK** | Surrogate key for the fact table (generated via `ROW_NUMBER`). |
| `company_id` | `INT` | **FK** | Foreign Key linking to `dim_company`. |
| `fiscal_period` | `DATE` | | The fiscal quarter end date (e.g., '2022-03-31'). Used for time-series analysis. |
| `revenue_pln_mln` | `DECIMAL` | | Total revenue in million PLN. |
| `net_income_pln_mln` | `DECIMAL` | | Net profit/loss in million PLN. |
| `ebitda_pln_mln` | `DECIMAL` | | EBITDA value in million PLN. |
| `ebit_pln_mln` | `DECIMAL` | | EBIT (Operating Income) in million PLN. |
